The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | New CM for Uttarakhand
                                                                                                               New CM for Uttarakhand
                            
	New Delhi, June 24: Ramesh Pokhriyal was today named the new chief minister of Uttarakhand after B.C. Khanduri stepped down following the BJP rout in the Lok Sabha elections in the state.        
	Pokhriyal, 51, was health minister under Khanduri.         
	Addressing the media, Pokhriyal said Khanduri would continue as the real chief minister. I have learnt politics from him. He is a big tree and I am going to work under his shadow and direction, the former journalist, who also wrote poetry, said.                                                                                                                                                                           
